Once you start thinking in terms of domains with their own physics, you realize “land, sea, air, space, and cyberspace” are just a handful of the many spaces humans navigate.

Here are some others that may deserve their own “physics.”

Semantic Space

The medium is meaning.

* Wind → analogy
* Gravity → core concepts
* Friction → ambiguity
* Compass → definitions
* Terrain → ontologies

This is very close to what you’ve been building with the Pantheon.

